1. Passing Props
Send data from parent → child
JSX
<Greeting name="Alice" />
JSX
function Greeting({ name }) {
  return <h2>Hello, {name}!</h2>;
}
👉 props = input to components
2. Multiple Props (PostCard)
JSX
function PostCard({ title, excerpt, author, date }) {
  return (
    <article>
      <h3>{title}</h3>
      <p>{excerpt}</p>
      <small>{author} | {date}</small>
    </article>
  );
}
Usage:
JSX
<PostCard title="React" excerpt="Learn React..." author="John" date="Jan 1" />
3. Rendering Lists (map + key)
JSX
{posts.map(post => (
  <PostCard key={post.id} {...post} />
))}
✔ Always use key (unique id)
4. Default Props
JSX
function Button({ text = "Click me", variant = "primary" }) {
  return <button className={variant}>{text}</button>;
}
Usage:
JSX
<Button /> // uses defaults
<Button text="Save" />
